    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-14T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762.65/100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-14T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 14, 1934—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 14—7:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. My telegrams numbers 112, June 9, 7 p.m., and 114, June 12, 7 p.m.<note
                        n="14" xml:id="d190fn14">Neither printed; see telegram No. 129, June 22, 1
                        p.m., from the Ambassador in Italy, <ref target="frus1934v01#pg_491">vol.
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 491</ref>.</note> Following
                    communiqué published this morning: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Since it has for some time been the desire of the Chief of the Italian
                            Government and of the Chancellor of the Reich to know each other <pb
                                facs="0323" n="223" xml:id="pg_223"/> personally and to discuss the
                            general political situation the two statesmen will meet toward the end
                            of the week in a city of northern Italy”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Headlines in the press this morning announce that the meeting will take place
                    today at Villa Pisconi in Stra near Venice.</p>
                <p>This morning’s <hi rend="italic">Messaggero</hi> intimates that Mussolini’s chief
                    preoccupation will be to pave the way for Germany’s return to the League of
                    Nations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
